  "body": "We should increase the coverage of the newly created clojure integration tests.\r\n\r\nOne of the most common use cases is to recover an account from a seed phrase, store the key on Keycard, and fetch the balance (on the Goerli test network)\r\n\r\nThe test steps that should be covered in the tests should be:\r\n\r\n1. Recover multiaccount from a seed phrase and choose Keycard as a key storage, log in\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/blob/823fce24570900cd2699fe679867fdf723c13561/src/status_im/integration_test.cljs#L182\r\n2. Simulate opening the wallet tab\r\n3. Make sure that the balance is updated\r\n\r\nWe want to achieve the closest coverage to what the UI is actually doing.\r\n\r\nTo simulate in the UI:\r\n\r\n1. Restore multiaccount from phrase `between alien slide inner squirrel recall popular million fork verb team runway`\r\n2. Choose Keycard as key storage during onboarding\r\n3. Open the wallet tab\r\n4. Make sure that there is 0.001 ETHGo, 2 STT on the balance",
